The paper discusses the development of a novel model for Interactive Question Answering (IQA) using neural network-based sequence-to-sequence models in an encoder-decoder framework. This falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning (ML), which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Specifically, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category as it covers topics related to NLP and ML. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories as they cover topics related to ML and deep learning. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category as it covers topics related to search and retrieval of information, which is relevant to IQA. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as it covers topics related to neural networks, which are used in the proposed model.
